result.adr_address: 2 Battery St, Jordan, Hong Kong
result.name: 新明記火鍋

reviews.text:
Excellent place for Hot Pot in Hong Kong. Seafood, Beef, Meat, Vegetables all  freshly available. Price is best value in Hong Kong.

Suggest a clear Base Pot Soup to start with. This meal just HK$600.
Nowhere available in Hong Kong with equivalent quality and quantity.
simple but fresh food, many choices of soup bases. Neighborhood casual atmosphere. Not expensive.
Good food at reasonable price for hotpot dining.

Fresh hotpot foodstuff especially beef. Getting expensive than 2 to 3 years ago. A smaller group of 2 to 3 people will feel this because of fixed charge items like soup base. Still good if you have more than 6 people.

A popular local hotpot place, Sun Meng Kei can get really rowdy and noisy with friends and families enjoying a night out with drinks and cheap food a plenty. If you are lucky, you might even catch a TVB star or two enjoying a late night supper after a long day of shooting. A perennial favorite of many Hong Kongers, the fundamentals of a great hotpot lie in a flavorful soup base and fresh ingredients to dunk and cook in the soup base. Sun Meng Kei doesn't fail in the variety of seafood, veggies and meat choices available to restaurant patrons. Prices are super reasonable, but.... soup's so~so taste wise, and I've seen fresher seafood served up (but it's not bad). I'd go there again with friends for a casual fun dinner, but it's not the place where you want to bring out of town guests or guests you wanna impress. There are better (albeit more expensive) hotpot places in Hong Kong for that.

result.name: 新明記火鍋

reviews.text:
用豬大骨和胡椒燉的湯底
胡椒味很濃郁但不嗆
手切肥牛就像溫體牛 很嫩
海鮮也很新鮮
值得一試
香港必吃打邊爐～現切肥牛，食材豐盛
待應服務態度一般，某一兩個人可能講係差，食物一般

如果佐敦打邊爐，只此一間，夠香港，夠地踎。
但今次牛肉唔太得，西洋菜餃朕味好似有尐酸，其他依然保持水準。
火锅材料新鮮，可以一試再試
